comments: McRae (WAS) and Nunn (MIA) briefly engage and separate off-ball.
Butler (MIA) makes marginal contact with Beal's (WAS) body at the start of his upward shooting motion during his driving shot.
Johnson (MIA) establishes a legal position in Smith's (WAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes a legal position in Butler's (MIA) path and firms up on his left leg.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact to Beal's (WAS) front in transition.

Dragic (MIA) momentarily places a hand to Smith's (WAS) side and he removes his hand as Smith begins his upward shooting motion. The body-to-body contact after the shot is released is considered incidental and does not affect Smith's ability to return to the floor.
Johnson (MIA) establishes a legal position in Smith's (WAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes a legal screening position in Jones Jr.'s (MIA) path and he firms up on his left leg when contact occurs.
Johnson (MIA) makes incidental contact with Mahinmi's (WAS) arm after cleanly dislodging the ball during his shot attempt at the rim.
Smith (WAS) briefly grasps Herro's (MIA) lower body as they disengage from the screen.
Smith (WAS) is initially in a legal guarding position and makes contact with the ball, Smith does not dislodge the ball before he lowers his arms.   Any subsequent contact is marginal.
Bertans (WAS) splits his feet.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes a legal position in McRae's (WAS) path and firms up on his right leg when contact occurs.
Mahinmi (WAS) makes marginal contact with Herro's (MIA) body during his shooting motion on the driving shot attempt.
Bertans (WAS) is not in a legal position when contact occurs with Butler (MIA) during the driving shot attempt.
Jones Jr. (MIA) and Beal (WAS) make incidental contact with one another off-ball.
Butler (MIA) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Beal's (WAS) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bonga (WAS) commits a take foul on Butler (MIA).
McRae (WAS) firms up in a legal picking position in Jones Jr.'s (MIA) path and he absorbs the contact.
Replay review of the foul called on Payton II (WAS) pursuant to a coachs challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
Johnson (MIA) makes incidental contact with Bertans (WAS) after the release on his jump shot attempt.
